nter for materials science of the department of commerces national institute of standards and technology he initiated numerous governmentindustry programs that became models for such cooperative efforts during his uc santa barbara and carnegie mellon university tenures he spunoff a number of high technology companies an internationally recognized authority on advanced technologies mehrabian also served as senior advisor in manufacturing and high technology processes to many fortune  companies mehrabian holds eight us and more than  foreign patents he has authored  technical papers and edited six books in the field of materials science and engineering his awards include election to the national academy of engineering nae a fellow and distinguished life member of the american society of metals international asm the henry marion howe medal of the asm and a fellow and leadership award recipient of the minerals metals and materials society tms his honorary degrees include scd from carnegie mellon and lhd from chatham college home  terms of use  careers  search  contact copyright   teledyne technologies incorporated all rights reserved  camino dos rios  thousand oaks ca    quote data provided by north american quotations inc robert mehrabian collaborative innovation centercorporate and institutional partnerships  carnegie mellon university robert mehrabian collaborative innovation centercorporate and institutional partnerships  carnegie mellon university carnegie mellon universitysearch only corporate and institutional partnerships submit carnegie mellon university search skip navigation and jump directly to page content highlighted partnershipsrobert mehrabian collaborative innovation centertenantsparking and directionssustainable designthe gates center for computer sciencegm collaborative research labdisney research labintel research pittsburghentertainment technology centercylab leaders in network securityuniversity partnership of pittsburghpoints of distinctionengagement opportunitiescontact us corporate and institutional partnerships  highlighted partnerships  robert mehrabian collaborative innovation center industrys home on campus robert mehrabian collaborative innovation center the vision of the robert mehrabian collaborative innovation center cic is to create the optimal environment to serve the next generation of university–industry collaboration the robert mehrabian cic is a fourstory squarefoot drylab research facility built in  to provide office and lab space for technology companies wishing to collaborate with carnegie mellon to create innovative new concepts and products for the marketplace the robert mehrabian cic is a partnership between carnegie mellon the carnegie museums and local economic development organizations and is funded with  million in commonwealth of pennsylvania tax support it also represents the hub of carnegie mellons engagement in the keystone innovation zone kiz program a program to accelerate economic growth and encourage collaboration between colleges universities local economic developers local government and businesses within our region the facility promotes regional economic development as carnegie mellon researchers work with industry to develop new technologies business ventures and jobs construction of the center was funded with state capital and department of community development funds carnegie mellon financing and support from the city of pittsburgh and the regional industrial development corporation as carnegie mellons first effort to create space on campus for joint research with industry the building is a celebration of the goals of the kiz program the building creates a nexus for industry federal and university research—supporting startups enhancing competitiveness for federal research funding and creating a landing zone for companies said mark kamlet carnegie mellon provost and senior vice president kamlet said the building is a hotbed for nextgeneration wireless and mobile computing robotics and trustworthy computing applications gates hillman center contact corporate and institutional partnerships helpful links corporate and institutional partnerships forbes avenue pittsburgh pa  carnegie mellon home highlighted partnershipscorporate and institutional partnerships  carnegie mellon university highlighted partnershipscorporate and institutional partnerships  carnegie mellon university carnegie mellon universitysearch only corporate and institutional partnerships submit carnegie mellon university search skip navigation and jump directly to page content highlighted partnershipsrobert mehrabian collaborative innovation centerthe gates center for computer sciencegm collaborative research labdisney research labintel research pittsburghentertainment technology centercylab leaders in network securityuniversity partnership of pittsburghpoints of distinctionengagement opportunitiescontact us corporate and institutional partnerships  highlighted partnerships matching worldclass research with industry leaders at the office of corporate and institutional partnerships we believe that collaboration drives innovation we work closely with faculty and researchers to keep up with the latest developments emerging from our pioneering labs and centers strategic partnerships at carnegie mellon provide your organization with unparalleled access to cuttingedge research and provide our students with invaluable realworld experience follow the links below to read about our most successful partnerships or contact us directly to learn about how your business can benefit from our expertise robert mehrabian collaborative innovation center the gates center for computer science general motorscarnegie mellon collaborative research labs disney research lab intel research pittsburgh entertainment technology center carnegie mellon cylab university partnership of pittsburgh contact corporate and institutional partnerships helpful links corporate and institutional partnerships for